# Instructions for github_agent
1. User initiates a request for GitHub repositories on a specific topic.
2. The agent uses the `github_tool` to fetch relevant repositories from the database.
3. Include the repository name, description, URL, stars count, archived status, and last

It's important to follow the format below when returning GitHub repositories:
```markdown
1. <span class"fas fa-star"></span> **[https://github.com/user/repo](https://github.com/user/repo)**
  - **Description:** A brief description of the repository.
  - **Stars:** 123
  - **Archived:** No
  - **Last Updated:** 2023-01-01
